  "time_ut": 1657181803,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "One hundred and three unrunable train boxes were brought from India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Parliamentary Committee on Government Accounts (COPA) has expressed strong displeasure regarding the huge waste of money allegedly caused by the importation of one hundred and three train carriages from India, which cannot be used in the railways of this country.",
        "COPA committee alleges that out of 160 railway carriages brought from India, 103 have not been put to use so far.",
        "In an inquiry made by the committee in this regard, the head of the railway department said that the vacuum break system exists in the railway carriages of this country.",
        "But they pointed out that the Air Break system is present in these new train carriages.",
        "The members asked who approved the importation of train carriages that are not suitable for this country. They further mentioned that the officials who took that decision should be held responsible for this.",
        "Also, there was a long discussion about the delayed importation of railway carriages that were planned to be brought to Sri Lanka under Indian loan subsidies in the year 2017.",
        "This information was revealed when the Committee on Government Accounts met recently (05) under the chairmanship of the Committee's Chairman, Member of Parliament Professor Tissa Witharana to examine the current and future plans planned under the Ministry of Transport and Highways to provide efficient transport services to the general public.",
        "Due to the rise in prices, Information was revealed in the COPA committee that the purchase of tires and other accessories for buses is in a problematic situation.",
        "Meanwhile, the ministry officials have alleged that the diesel issued for some private buses is being sold at a higher price.",
        "Here the committee has pointed out that this situation should be controlled and the public should be prevented from being inconvenienced.",
        "The committee pointed out that a system should be prepared to check whether the buses that get the oil are running. Especially GPS. The application of technology to buses was also discussed here.",
        "Also It was also discussed at length about the provision of diesel for private buses by filling stations owned by bus depots.",
        "In addition, in 2017, the Sri Lanka Railways Master Plan, which was planned on the financial basis of the Asian Development Bank, received USD. 1,056,555 was spent, but the grant was not included in the Ministry's budget or financial statements. Thus, the COPA Committee recommended the Railway Department to provide a report on this immediately.",
        "It was also discussed about combining railway transportation with new technology.",
        "The members of parliament Tissa Attanayake, Lasantha Alagiyawanna, Dayasiri Jayasekara, Dr. Sudarshanee Fernandopulle, Niroshan Perera, Duminda Dissanayake, Weerasumana Weerasinghe, Dr. Upul Galappathti, B.Y.G. Mr. Ratnasekara and Dr. Harini Amarasuriya participated."
      ],
